TESTS
 - Telling the starting player to move places a butterfly at the origin
 - Giving them another move makes them make another valid move
 - Do the above, but with a different location so we can't fake it
 
 
 
DESIGN RATIONALE
 - Take the player's move and simulate it
 - Get the set of all possible moves
 - Reduce it to the set of all possible VALID moves
 - Pick The Best Move(tm)
 - Profit